<br>
I myself am becoming a pilot for a position for a magor airline, and I can tell you that the control systems are totally different than that of most gaming simulators..<br>
<br>
You would need the most recent, most up to date sim, and the controls would have to be exactly the same, and the variables would have to also be the same. Not to mention, for larger aircraft like the ones that where hijacked the flight sim would have to be designed for that type of aircraft, imitation the cockpit controls to the letter..<br>
<br>
Now, first off the terrorist would need a modern computer to run a game/sim of this magnitude, and he would need the software, and that alone would give him only a basic grasp  of the plane he was flying..<br>
<br>
